#: ../../../Security.rst:201
msgid ""
"The parts of the LLVM Project which are currently treated as non-security "
"sensitive are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../Security.rst:203
msgid ""
"Language front-ends, such as clang, for which a malicious input file can "
"cause undesirable behavior. For example, a maliciously-crafter C or Rust "
"source file can cause arbitrary code to execute in LLVM. These parts of LLVM "
"haven't been hardened, and compiling untrusted code usually also includes "
"running utilities such as `make` which can more readily perform malicious "
"things."
msgstr ""

